.TH HACKTRIX 1 "2026-05-01" "hacktrix" "Security Research Tools"
.SH NAME
hacktrix \- search HackTricks and PayloadsAllTheThings for exploitation techniques
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hacktrix
.B \-f
.I TERM
[
.I TERM
\&...]
.br
.B hacktrix
.B \-p
.I TERM
[
.I TERM
\&...]
[
.B \-d
.I CONTEXT
]
.br
.B hacktrix
.B \-m
.I PATH
[
.B \-s
.I TERM
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hacktrix
searches local clones of HackTricks and PayloadsAllTheThings (PATT) for
exploitation techniques matching all provided search terms.
.PP
Use
.B \-f
to browse matching entries as a clean table (fast, no API cost).
Use
.B \-p
to send the matching content to Claude and receive a single,
syntax\-highlighted, ready\-to\-use payload with a recommendation.
Feed back errors or context with
.B \-d
to get an adapted payload on the next attempt.
Use
.B \-m
to copy a file from a
.B \-f
result to the current directory as plain text with markdown stripped.
Optionally scope the output to a specific section with
.BR \-s .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-find " " \fITERM\fR " [" \fITERM\fR ...]"
Search both sources for files containing all specified terms. Displays a
table with source tag, matched section title, and relative file path.
No Claude call is made. Fast and offline\-capable.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-payload " " \fITERM\fR " [" \fITERM\fR ...]"
Search both sources for files containing all specified terms, then send
the matched content to Claude. Claude selects the single most impactful
payload, syntax\-highlights it by language (JavaScript, PHP, Groovy,
Bash, Python, Java), and provides a one\-line recommendation.
Requires
.BR ANTHROPIC_API_KEY .
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-mirror " " \fIPATH\fR
Copy a file to the current directory as plain text with markdown stripped.
.I PATH
is the relative path exactly as shown in a
.B \-f
result. Paths with spaces must be quoted. Shell alias:
.BR htm .
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-section " " \fITERM\fR
Optional. Use with
.B \-m
to extract only the section whose heading contains
.IR TERM .
Extracts from the matched heading down to the next heading of equal or
higher level. Falls back to the full file if no matching heading is found.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-details " " \fICONTEXT\fR
Optional. Pass error output or additional context from a previous
.B \-p
attempt. Claude will analyse the failure and produce an adapted payload.
Only meaningful with
.BR \-p .
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
Required when using
.BR \-p " / " \-\-payload .
Obtain from console.anthropic.com.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/Tools/hacktricks
Local clone of the HackTricks knowledge base.
Clone with:
.B git clone https://github.com/HackTricks\-wiki/hacktricks ~/Tools/hacktricks
.TP
.I ~/Tools/payloadsallthethings
Local clone of PayloadsAllTheThings.
Clone with:
.B git clone https://github.com/swisskyrepo/PayloadsAllTheThings ~/Tools/payloadsallthethings
.SH EXAMPLES
Browse matching entries before committing to a payload:
.PP
.RS
.nf
hacktrix \-f ssti handlebars
hacktrix \-f lfi php windows iis
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate a payload directly:
.PP
.RS
.nf
hacktrix \-p ssti handlebars groovy rce
hacktrix \-p sqli union mysql
hacktrix \-p xss csp bypass reflected
hacktrix \-p lfi php windows iis read
.fi
.RE
.PP
Adapt after a failed attempt:
.PP
.RS
.nf
hacktrix \-p ssti handlebars groovy rce \-d "'require' is not defined"
hacktrix \-p sqli union mysql \-d "WAF blocking SELECT and UNION keywords"
hacktrix \-p lfi php \-d "../etc/passwd filtered, server returned 403"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Mirror a file from a \-f result (full file):
.PP
.RS
.nf
htm "Server Side Template Injection/JavaScript.md"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Mirror a specific section only:
.PP
.RS
.nf
htm "Server Side Template Injection/JavaScript.md" \-s handlebars
htm "File Inclusion/README.md" \-s php
.fi
.RE
.PP
Typical workflow:
.PP
.RS
.nf
hacktrix \-f ssti handlebars        # see what files match
htm "Server Side Template Injection/JavaScript.md" \-s handlebars  # grab the section
hacktrix \-p ssti handlebars groovy  # generate a payload
.fi
.RE
.SH NOTES
All search terms are AND\-matched against file content (case\-insensitive).
More specific terms return fewer files and produce more focused payloads.
If
.B \-p
returns no results, drop a term and try again.
.PP
Each
.B \-p
call costs approximately $0.001\(en$0.005 in Claude API credits
(claude\-sonnet\-4\-6, ~200\(en500 tokens output).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR searchsploit (1),
.BR msfconsole (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Written by jhaxx.
